Content-Type callbacks are callbacks defined per content-type of the request. So if you send a application/json request to the server you might want it to respond one way rather than if text/html is sent.

I implemented the callbacks as such:

```
    get('/', function() {
            this.content('html', function() {
                    return 'this is some html'
            })
            this.content('json', function() {
                    return 'this is some json'
            })
    })
```

You can check it on on my fork here: [http://github.com/rmontgomery429/express/tree/content_type_callbacks](http://github.com/rmontgomery429/express/tree/content_type_callbacks)

Let me know what you think.

